<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,151,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">Notes.</emphasis>
This taxon was first described by Baker as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker" authorityName="Baker" box="[893,1111,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[893,1038,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">M. variabilis</emphasis>
Baker
</taxonomicName>
but distinctive differences in the male genitalia of the nominotypical variety (subspecies) warrant elevation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Zahniser" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1118,1265,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[1118,1265,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">M. simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to status as a separate, valid species. A cotype from Baker's type series is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[1054,1157,223,248]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">lectotype</typeStatus>
to fix the identity of the species.
</paragraph>
